tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All hematological parameters are within normal limits except for a slightly decreased MCV (microcytosis) and a markedly elevated platelet distribution width (PDW). These findings may suggest early or mild microcytic anemia or increased platelet size variability, possibly due to reactive changes. Correlation with clinical context and iron studies may be considered if clinically indicated.
